★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────
- The implementation uses a two-call pattern: GetActiveSprint(boardID) → GetSprintIssueKeys(sprintID),
  caching the combined result under a board-scoped key (sprint_board_<id>.json). This avoids
  caching at the sprint-ID level, which would require knowing the sprint ID before the cache check.
- The json.RawMessage trick in cacheEntry.Value allows readCache/writeCache to be fully generic
  over any JSON-serializable type — both []string (sprint keys) and string (issue type) reuse
  the same helpers.
─────────────────────────────────────────────────
